label.value: microarray ELISA measuring Chikungunya IgM antibody

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that uses a microarray as the solid support and detects the IgM antibody that binds Chikungunya.

label.value: organism

definition.value: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

label.value: comet assay

definition.value: An assay that measures DNA damage (DNA breakage) in eucaryotic cells exposed to a challenge by determining the size and shape of DNA migration by detecting fluorescently labeled DNA from a cell placed in an electric field using gel electrophoresis

label.value: PCR-SSCP assay

definition.value: An assay that identifies DNA sequence variation (mutation, deletion, insertions) in target DNA sequences amplified using polymerase chain reaction using gel electrophoresis and denaturating conditions

label.value: tumor grading

definition.value: An assay that determines the grade (severity/stage) of a tumor sample, used in cancer biology to describe abnormalities/qualities of tumor cells or tissues. Values can be described by terms from NCI Thesaurus.

label.value: assay detecting a molecular label

definition.value: An assay that detects the presence or a quality of a molecular label which is a proxy for the detection of the molecular target to which the label is attached

label.value: histological assay

definition.value: An assay that uses visual examination of cells or tissue (or images of them) to make an assessment regarding a quality of the cells or tissue. This assay can include steps of staining, imaging, and judgement.

label.value: substance detection assay

definition.value: An assay that detects a specified substance

label.value: longitudinal mass measurement assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the mass of a material at two or more time points

label.value: enzyme-linked immunospot assay

definition.value: A cytometry assay in which cells are cultured on a surface coated with a capture antibody binding a secretory material of interest which subsequently gets stained resulting in a spot for each cell producing the secretory material of interest.

label.value: 3D structure determination assay

definition.value: An assay that determines the 3-dimensional configuration of an input material.

label.value: sequencing assay

definition.value: An assay the uses chemical or biochemical means to infer the sequence of a biomaterial

label.value: ELISPOT assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-2 production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunospot assay that detects interleukin-2 production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring binding of a T cell epitope:MHC:TCR complex

definition.value: A T cell epitope assay that measures the binding of T cell receptor to an epitope.

label.value: ELISPOT assay measuring epitope specific interferon-gamma production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunospot assay that detects interferon-gamma production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring qualitative binding of a T cell epitope:MHC:TCR complex

definition.value: An assay that detects the binding of a MHC:epitope complex with a T cell receptor, and produces a qualitative measurement of the binding as an output.

label.value: assay measuring MHC ligand processing and presentation

definition.value: A MHC ligand assay that determines what ligands are processed and loaded onto MHC molecules by eluting ligands and identifying them.

label.value: assay measuring binding of a MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A MHC ligand assay that detects the binding of a ligand to an MHC molecule.

label.value: assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope assay that measures the binding of an antibody receptor to an epitope.

label.value: immune epitope assay

definition.value: An assay that detects the binding of an epitope to an adaptive immune receptor, or an immune process resulting from such a binding event, or characterizes the structrue of the complex resulting from such a binding event.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific cytokine production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope assay that detects cytokine production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific T cell killing

definition.value: A T cell epitope dependent biological activity assay that detects the killing of an antigen presenting cell (APC) by a T cell whose TCR recognizes an epitope presented by the APC.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific proliferation of T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope dependent biological activity assay that detects T cell proliferation.

label.value: 51 chromium assay measuring epitope specific T cell killing

definition.value: A chromium release assay that detects the killing of an antigen presenting cell (APC) by a T cell whose TCR recognizes an epitope presented by the APC.
